prompt:
Explain how to make an easy dinner for four people using ingredients that are already available in the fridge and pantry.
An example of such a meal could be spaghetti Bolognese with tomato sauce, garlic bread, and salad. For this meal, you will need:
- 1 can (400g) of tomatoes;
- 1 small onion;
- 2 cloves of garlic;
- 500g of minced beef or pork;
- A small amount of olive oil for frying;
- Salt and pepper to taste;
- 500g of spaghetti noodles;
- 1 loaf of bread (about 4 slices);
- Some lettuce, tomatoes, cucumbers, and maybe olives for the salad.
